Hardware Acceleration

     I just had Direct TV's All Home DVR. I want to be able to watch
     programs from my PC but it requires software from Direct TV. I tried
     to Download the software but keep getting an error message that
     tells me I have to update my video driver. I have a Sapphire Radeon
     X1600 Pro and Sapphire Radeon X1600 Pro Secondary.
     I bhave downloaded the latest driver but I still keep getting an
     error message. This is what I get.
     "Problem: No Hardware Decoder detected.
     Why do I need hardware acceleration and what can I do to fix this?
     DIRECTV2PC applies the hardware protection mechanism on protected
     content using hardware acceleration technology. DIRECTV2PC cannot
     play the video content on your output device if it cannot apply the
     hardware protection mechanism.
     Problem: Screen Capture Protection. NO
     To solve this problem, try updating your graphics card driver. If
     your computers graphics card driver does not currently support
     hardware acceleration, try modifying your driver settings.
     Why did I receive a message that screen capture protection is not
     enabled and what can I do to fix this?
     Your computers graphics card driver does not currently support
     screen capture protection. Try updating your graphics card driver or
     modifying your driver settings if you could not apply screen capture
     protection on the video."
     I am not sure what "hardware acceleration" is or "screen capture
     protection".
     I also don't know what card to go to should the really be the
     problem. ASny help out there for an Old guy?
     Thanks
       [42]Reply With Quote Reply With Quote [43]Share on Google+
